<date box="[596,749,1635,1659]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" value="1987-08-05">Aug. 5, 1987</date>
; collected by James A. Scott”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1440,1699,1883]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,743,1699,1723]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
Cliff Ferris (pers. comm.) stated this subspecies may be a redecoration of the form known as 
<taxonomicName box="[599,807,1731,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="nikias">
<emphasis box="[599,807,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">S. hesperis nikias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which has since been synonymized under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="electa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">S. hesperis electa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Scott, J. A. &amp; N. G. Kondla &amp; S. M. Spomer" box="[303,503,1763,1787]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref45136" refString="Scott, J. A., N. G. Kondla, and S. M. Spomer. 1998. Speyeria hesperis and Speyeria atlantis are distinct species. Papilio 8: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1998">Scott et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Adult wingspan is on average 
<quantity box="[889,976,1763,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1440,1699,1883]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
